This paper presents a new learnable dynamics model for model-based control, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. Given that the paper focuses on the development of a new neural network architecture, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of the proposed model for control tasks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of the model for partially observable scenarios, which is a common problem in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Furthermore, the paper includes experiments with visual inputs, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed model for control tasks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-field of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
